Sam Schmidt, a quadriplegic, was paralyzed from the neck down after crashing during a test in Orlando in 2000 .
The modified 2014 Corvette C7 Stingray was a modified version of a modified 2014 model that allowed Schmidt to navigate the car independently using only his head and mouth .
Schmidt took to the course about an hour before the Grand Prix and did nearly two laps around the 11-turn circuit .